#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn25.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn25.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 25 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 25 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn25.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Cakkhuvagga "
msgstr "1. The Eye "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn25.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Cakkhusutta "
msgstr "1. The Eye "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.225, sc1
msgctxt "sn25.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn25.1:1.2"
msgid "“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the eye is impermanent, perishing, and changing. "

msgctxt "sn25.1:1.3"
msgid "sotaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi; "
msgstr "The ear, "

msgctxt "sn25.1:1.4"
msgid "ghānaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi; "
msgstr "nose, "

#. VAR: vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī → viparināmi aññathābhāvi (bj) | vipariṇāminī aññathābhāvinī (?)
msgctxt "sn25.1:1.5"
msgid "jivhā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī; "
msgstr "tongue, "

msgctxt "sn25.1:1.6"
msgid "kāyo anicco vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi; "
msgstr "body, "

msgctxt "sn25.1:1.7"
msgid "mano anicco vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī. "
msgstr "and mind are impermanent, perishing, and changing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn25.1:1.8"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati—ayaṃ vuccati saddhānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ; "
msgstr "Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person. "

msgctxt "sn25.1:1.9"
msgid "abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya; "
msgstr "They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm. "

#. VAR: abhabbo ca → abhabbova (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn25.1:1.10"
msgid "abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti. "
msgstr "They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry. "

# NOTE: Quotes in MS are incorrect.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn25.1:2.1"
msgid "Yassa kho, bhikkhave, ime dhammā evaṃ paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘dhammānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ; "
msgstr "Someone who accepts these principles after considering them with a degree of wisdom is called a follower of the teachings. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person. "

msgctxt "sn25.1:2.2"
msgid "abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya; "
msgstr "They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm. "

msgctxt "sn25.1:2.3"
msgid "abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti’. "
msgstr "They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn25.1:2.4"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ pajānāti evaṃ passati, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano’”ti. "
msgstr "Someone who understands and sees these principles is called a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn25.1:2.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
